Russian Equity Movers: Gazprom, Norilsk, Rosneft Are Active

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-06-22T09:29:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/russian-equity-movers-gazprom-norilsk-rosneft-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  dropped 0.6
percent to 1,625.84 as of 12:43 p.m. in Moscow, poised for the
lowest close since May 26. The dollar-denominated RTS Index
declined 0.3 percent to 1,866.40.  The following are among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX) declined after Kommersant-Ukraine
reported the gas export monopoly will agree to lower the price
Ukraine pays for natural-gas deliveries if Gazprom and state-
controlled NAK Naftogaz Ukrainy merge, citing unidentified
officials from Gazprom and Ukraine’s Energy and Coal Ministry.
The stock dropped 0.6 percent to 199.85 rubles.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX) fell after the company’s
directors elsected Andrei Bugrov as chairman, tilting the board
away from billionaire Oleg Deripaska and toward rival
shareholder  Vladimir Potanin  in a fight to control  Russia ’s
biggest mining company. The shares lost 0.8 percent to 6,867
rubles.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX), OAO  Tatneft (TATN)  (TATN3 RX) and OAO
Surgutneftegas (SNGSP RX) declined as oil retreated as much as
86 cents to $93.31 a barrel. Rosneft lost 0.9 percent to 233.1
rubles, Tatneft fell 0.8 percent to 168.79 rubles and
Surgutneftegas sank 0.4 percent to 27.141 rubles.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  